00:26:57.929 --> 00:27:02.225
Filled with color

00:27:03.059 --> 00:27:04.477
Like a gentle painting

00:27:04.561 --> 00:27:11.234
Filled with color

00:27:22.912 --> 00:27:25.248
That was so moving!

00:27:25.331 --> 00:27:26.541
I didn't understand anything,

00:27:26.624 --> 00:27:28.209
but was that a love song?

00:27:29.127 --> 00:27:30.128
Yes.

00:27:31.254 --> 00:27:34.549
But for me,

00:27:35.633 --> 00:27:39.053
it's a farewell song, in a way.

00:27:40.930 --> 00:27:42.515
Thank you for the food.

00:27:49.481 --> 00:27:52.400
{\an8}SLIDE TO ANSWER

00:27:53.943 --> 00:27:55.987
Yes? Hello?

00:27:57.864 --> 00:27:59.365
Yes, that's correct.

00:28:01.159 --> 00:28:01.993
What?

00:28:10.543 --> 00:28:11.836
Good work, Taiga.

00:28:11.920 --> 00:28:14.047
You too, Masumi.

00:28:14.130 --> 00:28:16.591
Want to get some drinks after this?

00:28:17.300 --> 00:28:19.010
No, I think I'll pass today.

00:28:19.093 --> 00:28:21.638
Okay. Maybe next time, then.

00:28:26.142 --> 00:28:27.435
Masumi.

00:28:30.730 --> 00:28:34.275
I really appreciate you
choosing me for this event.

00:28:35.860 --> 00:28:38.321
I was happy to be able
to engage with athletes

00:28:38.404 --> 00:28:40.365
in a different way than my college days.

00:28:41.658 --> 00:28:42.742
Yeah.

00:28:43.284 --> 00:28:47.163
I'm happy, too, to hear those words
coming from you.

00:28:47.997 --> 00:28:49.165
Thanks.

00:28:49.249 --> 00:28:50.208
Yeah.

00:28:56.631 --> 00:28:57.674
Hey…

00:28:58.591 --> 00:28:59.509
Huh?

00:29:00.093 --> 00:29:04.013
I'm sorry. I'm starting to like you again.

00:29:06.057 --> 00:29:07.141
What?

00:29:08.351 --> 00:29:10.854
I'm telling you,
because I don't want any more regrets.

00:29:11.938 --> 00:29:15.775
I do feel bad telling you this when things
aren't going well with your girlfriend.

00:29:19.070 --> 00:29:20.363
I feel like,

00:29:21.030 --> 00:29:23.366
this time,
we'll be able to support each other

00:29:23.449 --> 00:29:25.577
and make things work.

00:29:29.414 --> 00:29:30.623
Support?

00:29:31.583 --> 00:29:32.458
Yeah.

00:29:33.167 --> 00:29:34.544
Back then,

00:29:35.253 --> 00:29:38.006
I ignored your passion for track,

00:29:38.089 --> 00:29:39.966
and rushed you and hurt you.

00:29:42.218 --> 00:29:45.013
All I wanted was for you to say…

00:29:46.306 --> 00:29:49.225
I wish you would've accepted me,
even just for a second.

00:29:49.809 --> 00:29:51.019
Sorry.

00:29:52.562 --> 00:29:54.272
It's too difficult for me.

00:29:56.399 --> 00:29:58.192
I don't need an answer right away.

00:29:59.444 --> 00:30:00.445
Just think about it.

00:30:02.322 --> 00:30:03.531
Bye. Thanks for everything.

00:30:24.636 --> 00:30:28.097
{\an8}RIN

00:32:34.724 --> 00:32:36.309
Taiga, I'm sorry.

00:32:40.605 --> 00:32:41.564
Rin!

00:32:50.907 --> 00:32:52.492
{\an8}Finally, I found you!

00:32:52.575 --> 00:32:53.534
{\an8}Thank goodness.

00:32:54.327 --> 00:32:55.369
Why?

00:32:56.954 --> 00:32:59.499
Rin? What's the matter?

00:33:11.844 --> 00:33:12.887
Are you okay?

00:33:26.025 --> 00:33:27.151
Taiga,

00:33:28.444 --> 00:33:30.655
why are you so nice?

00:33:32.156 --> 00:33:33.199
What?

00:33:35.034 --> 00:33:37.161
I said hurtful things to you.

00:33:38.663 --> 00:33:40.206
Well that's…

00:33:41.332 --> 00:33:43.417
because I made you say them, in a way.

00:33:46.462 --> 00:33:47.588
I…

00:33:48.339 --> 00:33:50.299
was too dependent on you.

00:33:51.050 --> 00:33:53.845
Thinking about my future
made me anxious and irritated,

00:33:54.637 --> 00:33:56.806
and I took all of it out on you.

00:33:59.892 --> 00:34:01.644
I'm really sorry.

00:34:08.317 --> 00:34:09.944
When I was in a rut,

00:34:10.903 --> 00:34:13.030
you never criticized me.

00:34:13.114 --> 00:34:16.576
You acknowledged my feelings
and encouraged me, remember?

00:34:18.786 --> 00:34:20.163
But when it was my turn,

00:34:21.789 --> 00:34:27.003
I pressured you and hurt you.

00:34:28.838 --> 00:34:29.964
I'm really sorry.

00:34:38.139 --> 00:34:39.974
Your words…

00:34:40.850 --> 00:34:42.101
Your smile…

00:34:43.811 --> 00:34:47.899
Everything about you gave me strength.

00:34:50.985 --> 00:34:52.653
So this time,

00:34:53.863 --> 00:34:56.991
I want to support you.

00:35:00.995 --> 00:35:02.121
I don't want…

00:35:05.124 --> 00:35:06.751
to let you go yet.

00:35:08.794 --> 00:35:09.795
That's…

00:35:12.340 --> 00:35:13.507
how I feel.

00:35:19.764 --> 00:35:20.932
Earlier,

00:35:23.059 --> 00:35:26.479
a person from an advertising agency who
praised my work at the cultural festival,

00:35:26.979 --> 00:35:28.314
called me.

00:35:29.565 --> 00:35:32.652
They asked if I wanted
to start working as an intern.

00:35:34.737 --> 00:35:36.322
That's great!

00:35:37.198 --> 00:35:38.783
Good for you!

00:35:42.245 --> 00:35:44.288
I wanted to tell you, Taiga.

00:35:46.165 --> 00:35:48.292
Whether I'm feeling sad,

00:35:49.168 --> 00:35:51.254
or feeling happy, or anything,

00:35:53.256 --> 00:35:55.758
the first person I think of is you.

00:35:56.842 --> 00:35:59.011
Everything brings me back to you.

00:36:03.849 --> 00:36:05.434
I like you, Taiga.

00:36:24.161 --> 00:36:25.329
Me too.

00:36:26.831 --> 00:36:28.749
I was thinking about you the whole time.

00:36:31.919 --> 00:36:35.464
I'm sorry for breaking up with you.

00:36:44.056 --> 00:36:45.057
Rin.

00:36:47.643 --> 00:36:52.356
Will you go out with me again?

00:36:56.652 --> 00:36:57.737
Yes.

00:37:10.666 --> 00:37:11.792
You're hungry?

00:37:13.419 --> 00:37:14.587
I'm hungry.

00:37:23.012 --> 00:37:24.263
{\an8}Look, Rin!

00:37:26.390 --> 00:37:27.350
{\an8}It stopped raining.

00:37:47.995 --> 00:37:49.872
{\an8}- Cheers.
- Cheers.

00:37:56.003 --> 00:37:57.129
It's good.

00:37:57.213 --> 00:37:59.340
We finally got to drink it.

00:37:59.423 --> 00:38:01.759
Taiga, thank you for the dak gomtang.

00:38:01.842 --> 00:38:03.344
It was really kkulmat!

00:38:05.221 --> 00:38:07.264
{\an8}But did you know your Korean message said,

00:38:08.599 --> 00:38:11.227
{\an8}"If you like me, eat it"

00:38:12.478 --> 00:38:13.354
{\an8}in a commanding tone?

00:38:13.437 --> 00:38:14.730
{\an8}What?

00:38:14.814 --> 00:38:15.815
{\an8}It's okay

00:38:16.399 --> 00:38:19.235
{\an8}if you want to act like a cocky guy
once in a while.

00:38:19.318 --> 00:38:20.152
{\an8}Let's go.

00:38:22.029 --> 00:38:23.155
{\an8}Where to?

00:38:23.239 --> 00:38:24.198
{\an8}Home.

00:38:24.740 --> 00:38:25.866
{\an8}What?

00:38:28.369 --> 00:38:29.995
{\an8}Hey, wait!

00:38:33.040 --> 00:38:33.999
Are you making fun of me?

00:38:34.083 --> 00:38:34.917
It's a compliment.

00:38:35.000 --> 00:38:36.419
I like that about you.

00:38:36.502 --> 00:38:38.003
- Hey!
- Move.

00:38:38.087 --> 00:38:39.213
How stupid can you be?

00:38:39.296 --> 00:38:40.589
{\an8}It's almost sad.

